properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued March 2 at 11:57AM PST until March 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 20 to 35 mph with gusts to 60 mph. Isolated
gusts to 75 mph in wind-prone areas.

* WHERE...San Bernardino and Riverside County Valleys-The Inland
Empire, San Bernardino County Mountains, Santa Ana Mountains
and Foothills and Orange County Inland Areas.

* WHEN...Until noon PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines.
Power outages are possible. Travel will be hazardous, especially
for high profile vehicles due to sudden and strong cross winds.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strongest wind gust potential will be later
this evening through Tuesday morning.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, Use extra caution if you must
drive a high-profile vehicle and possibly postpone travel until
after the strongest wind potential.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON PST TUESDAY
